 a particularly popular name in England and France in the later Middle Ages; notable bearers in England include the poet  Geoffrey Chaucer  (  <i>c.</i>1340–1400 ) and in Wales the chronicler  Geoffrey  of Monmouth (  d. 1155 ). The original form and meaning of the name is disputed. According to one theory, it is merely a variant of   Godfrey ;  others derive the first part from the Germanic word <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Geoffroy de Nedonchel was born in 1130, in Nédonchel, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, his father, Guyon de Nédonchel II, was 26 and his mother, Avicie de Desvres, was 16. He married Arlette de Humières about 1153. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1199, in his hometown, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1130–1199":"1130–1199","1138–1192":"1138–1192","1155–1201":"1155–1201","1104–1162":"1104–1162","1114–1159":"1114–1159","1138":"1138","1159":"1159","1104":"1104","1114":"1114","1201":"1201","(VERS 1153)":"umbes 1153","1155":"1155","1199":"1199","before 1130":"enne 1130","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1192":"1192","Nédonchel, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Nédonchel, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Europe":"Europe","Nédonchel, Pas-Calés, Heuts-d'Franche, Française":"Nédonchel, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1130–1199":"1130–1199","1138–1192":"1138–1192","1155–1201":"1155–1201","1104–1162":"1104–1162","1114–1159":"1114–1159","1138":"1138","1159":"1159","1104":"1104","1114":"1114","1201":"1201","(VERS 1153)":"noin 1153","1155":"1155","1199":"1199","before 1130":"ennen vuotta 1130","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1192":"1192","Nédonchel, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Nédonchel, Pas-de-C